Service revenue increased during 2020 largely due to growth in phone subscribers and connected devices, offset by declines in
international roaming revenue due to reduced travel during the pandemic. Successful offers aimed at customer retention contributed to
subscriber growth and lower churn.
ARPU
Average revenue per subscriber (ARPU) decreased primarily due to the decline in international roaming and waived fees.
Churn
The effective management of subscriber churn is critical to our ability to maximize revenue growth and to maintain and improve
margins. Postpaid churn and postpaid phone-only churn were lower in 2020 due to migrations to unlimited plans, continued network
improvements, subscriber retention offers in the fourth quarter, and lower overall involuntary disconnects.1
